# CODEOWNERS — review gates on Duhem.
#
# Spec: onsager-ai/duhem#36. The `verifications/**` gate is the
# Duhem half of the asymmetric-trust seam (`docs/duhem-spec.md`
# §11.2): a Verification Definition is the human commitment about
# what "done" means for a feature, and edits to one must pass
# through a Duhem maintainer. A consumer repo's PR cannot smuggle
# in a self-attesting edit to its own check by opening a PR on
# this repo.
#
# Pair this file with branch-protection rules on `main` that
# require CODEOWNERS approval; the file alone is advisory.

# Catch-all default — any path without a more specific rule still
# routes to a maintainer.
*                       @tikazyq

# Verification Definitions. The first deployment of the trust
# boundary; the only path that exists today is the
# create-spec-plan dogfood, but the glob covers any future VD.
/verifications/         @tikazyq

# Schema and judge — the wire format and the verdict engine. A
# regression here would corrupt every downstream verdict.
/crates/duhem-schema/   @tikazyq
/crates/duhem-judge/    @tikazyq

# The action that wires Duhem into a consumer's PR pipeline.
# A change here ships into every consumer that pins a new tag.
/.github/actions/run/   @tikazyq
